---
import Layout from '@/layouts/main.astro';
import { idJoinWaitlistUrl } from '@/lib/consts';

const title = 'Why ASIMOV - Architecture & privacy | ASIMOV Systems';
const description =
  'How ASIMOV works: public and personal storage physically separated, your Personal Context Graph, and inferential connections—privacy-first personal intelligence.';
const canonicalUrl = 'https://asimov.systems/why-asimov';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalUrl} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={canonicalUrl} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://asimov.systems/og-image.png" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:site" content="@ASIMOV_Protocol" />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="py-20 lg:py-32">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 lg:px-6">
      <header class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase">
          Why ASIMOV
        </p>
        <h1 class="font-calSans mt-2 text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
          How we give you clarity without compromising your data
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 text-lg">
          Public and personal storage are physically separated. The ASIMOV PI suite uses both to
          build your context graph and inferential connections—without exposing your private data to
          the shared layer.
        </p>
      </header>

      <figure class="border-border bg-card/50 mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl rounded-xl border p-4 md:p-6">
        <img
          src="/assets/AsimovPIdatadiagram.png"
          alt="ASIMOV PI architecture: public data sources and ingestion pipeline to cloud cache; your personal cache (private data) combined and linked into your Personal Context Graph; ASIMOV Intelligence Tools output."
          class="w-full rounded-lg"
          width="1200"
          height="800"
        />
        <figcaption class="text-muted-foreground mt-3 text-center text-sm">
          Public and personal storage, combined and linked into your Personal Context Graph,
          powering ASIMOV Intelligence Tools.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div
        class="border-border bg-card/50 mx-auto mt-16 max-w-3xl space-y-12 rounded-xl border p-6 md:p-10"
      >
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">1. Public side</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 max-w-3xl text-base">
            Public data sources (websites, social networks, public APIs, news and events) feed into
            an ingestion pipeline. That pipeline fills the ASIMOV Cloud Cache—a shared public
            storage layer. Everyone benefits from the same useful context (e.g. identity
            recognition, public knowledge).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">2. Your side</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 max-w-3xl text-base">
            When you sign up and get a name, we create your personal storage—the ASIMOV Personal
            Cache. It is physically separate from the public storage. Only your private data lives
            here (contacts, private socials, files). Public and personal storage servers are
            physically separated.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">3. Combined and linked</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 max-w-3xl text-base">
            The system combines and links public cache and your personal cache (without mixing the
            underlying stores). That produces your Personal Context Graph—one place where your
            private data and what exists in the cloud are connected for you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">4. ASIMOV Personal Intelligence tools</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 max-w-3xl text-base">
            The ASIMOV suite of Personal Intelligence tools (smart search, AI insights,
            recommendations, identity recognition) runs on that graph. The system creates
            inferential connections between your personal data and what’s already in the cloud—so
            you get powerful, contextual intelligence while your private data stays in your personal
            storage.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-muted-foreground mx-auto mt-10 max-w-3xl text-center text-base italic">
        One line: Public and personal storage servers are physically separated; the PI suite uses
        both to build your context graph and inferential connections, without exposing your private
        data to the shared layer.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-16 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/product"
          class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90 inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md px-6 text-sm font-medium"
        >
          Explore ASIMOV PI
        </a>
        <a
          href={idJoinWaitlistUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="border-input bg-background hover:bg-accent inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md border px-6 text-sm font-medium"
        >
          Join waitlist
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
